'''Bahamas men's national softball team''' is the national team for [[Bahamas]].  The 1988 World Championships were held in [[Saskatoon, Canada]].  The team played 13 games in the round robin round.  They finished sixth overall.<ref name=batter-up-194>{{cite book|pages=194–195|chapter=Appendix N|title=Batter up! : the history of softball in Australia|first1=Lynn|last1=Embrey |location=Bayswater, Vic.|publisher=Australian Softball Federation|year=1995}}</ref><ref name=1988champs>{{cite web|url=http://www.isfsoftball.org/english/events/88_mens_wc.asp |title=1988 ISF Men's World Championship |publisher=International Softball Federation |date=2013 |accessdate=7 February 2014 |location=United States |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140225213055/http://www.isfsoftball.org/english/events/88_mens_wc.asp |archivedate=25 February 2014 }}</ref>   The team competed at the 1996 [[ISF Men's World Championship]] in [[Midland, Michigan]] where they finished with 5 wins and 5 losses.<ref name=1996champs>{{cite web|url=http://www.isfsoftball.org/english/events/96_mens_wc.asp |title=1996 ISF Men's World Championship |publisher=International Softball Federation |date=2013 |accessdate=7 February 2014 |location=United States |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140225213058/http://www.isfsoftball.org/english/events/96_mens_wc.asp |archivedate=25 February 2014 }}</ref> 

