'''Football Club Tevragh-Zeïna''' ({{lang-ar|نادي تفرغ زينة لكرة القدم}}) is a [[Mauritania|Mauritanean]] [[football (soccer)|football]] club based in the [[Tevragh-Zeina]] district of [[Nouakchott]]. The club was founded in 2005.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20110304231459/http://fr.cafonline.com/competition/coupe-de-la-confederation_2010/news/8445-zeina-tevragh-fleuron-du-football-mauritanien.html Zeina Tevragh, fleuron du football mauritanien]</ref>

== History ==
<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Fctevraghzeinateam2016.jpeg|thumb|right|FC Tevragh Zeina in an Away Game during the 16-17 mauritanean League]] -->
In 2009, ASC Tevragh-Zeïna reached the final of the [[Coupe du Président de la République]] but lost to [[ASAC Concorde]] 5–4 on penalties after the game ended 0–0.<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesm/maur09.html Coupe du Président de la République &#91;National Cup&#93;]</ref> In 2010, they won the competition, beating FC Feu Mini 3–0 in the final.<ref>[http://www.magharebia.com/cocoon/awi/xhtml1/en_GB/features/awi/features/2010/10/17/feature-01 T. Zeina win Mauritania Cup]</ref> By winning the Cup, they qualified for the [[2011 CAF Confederation Cup]].

On February 28, 2011, Tevragh-Zeïna became the first club from [[Mauritania]] since 1994 to advance in continental competition after beating [[AS Real Bamako]] of Mali 1–0 on aggregate in the preliminary round of the [[2011 CAF Confederation Cup]].<ref>[https://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/clubfootball/news/newsid=1390117.html Cup sees rare Mauritania club success]</ref> However, they were eliminated in the following round after losing 3–1 on aggregate to [[JS Kabylie]] of Algeria.<ref>[http://www.cafonline.com/competition/confederation-cup_2010/news/8842-nessakh-brace-powers-jsk-into-next-round.html Nessakh brace powers JSK into next round]</ref>

Tevragh-Zeina won the [[2014–15 Mauritanian Premier League]] title after defeating Sélibaby 4–0 in the last round and overtaking their rivals [[ASC Snim|Cansado]] who came second with a difference of one point. As a result, they qualified for the [[2016 CAF Champions League]].

== Achievements ==
