{{Infobox stadium |stadium_name=Grundman Stadium |image=Ramhash 049.jpg |image_size=250px |caption= |location=[[Ramat HaSharon]], [[Israel]] |opened=1998 |renovated=2012 |owner=[[Ramat HaSharon|Municipality of Ramat HaSharon]] |operator=[[Ramat HaSharon|Municipality of Ramat HaSharon]] |construction_cost= |surface = Grass |architect= |former_names= |tenants=[[Ironi Nir Ramat HaSharon F.C.]], [[Hapoel Morasha Ramat HaSharon F.C.]] |seating_capacity=4,300 }} '''Grundman Stadium''' ({{lang-he|אצטדיון גרונדמן}}, ''Itztadion Grundman'') is a [[Association football|football]] [[stadium]] in [[Ramat HaSharon]], [[Israel]].<ref name="ynetarticle" /> It is the home stadium of [[Ironi Nir Ramat HaSharon F.C.|Ironi Nir Ramat HaSharon]]. The stadium holds 4,300 and was built in 1998 and been renovated in 2012.<ref name="ynetarticle">{{cite news|url=http://www.ynet.co.il/articles/0,7340,L-4198605,00.html|title=Ramat HaSharon: The police approved Grundman stadium |publisher=Yedihut Achronot |work=Ynet! |accessdate=5 May 2012 |date=5 March 2012 |language=Hebrew}}</ref>
The stadium is named after former football player and manager [[Ya'akov Grundman]], who played for [[Bnei Yehuda Tel Aviv F.C.|Bnei Yehuda]] and managed [[Israel national football team|Israel]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://football.org.il/Archive/Articles/Pages/oArticle221.aspx |title=Ramat HaSharon Stadium named after Ya'akov Grundman |accessdate=5 May 2012 |date=15 December 2004 |language=Hebrew}}</ref>
