'''Keith Cronin''' (born 18 July 1986) is an [[Irish people|Irish]] [[Rallying|rally driver]] and 4 time winner of the [[British Rally Championship]]. He won the [[2009 British Rally Championship season|2009 British Rally Championship]],  in his first year in the series, defeating multiple champion [[Mark Higgins (driver)|Mark Higgins]] in his privately entered TTec Rally Prep, Cronin Motorsport [[Mitsubishi Lancer Evolution#Evolution IX|Mitsubishi Lancer Evolution IX]]. Cronin successfully defended his title in [[2010 British Rally Championship season|2010]] driving a [[Subaru Impreza]].<ref name="Profile">{{cite web|title= e-WRC Profile|url=http://www.ewrc-results.com/profile.php?p=7513&t=Keith-Cronin}}</ref> After missing the 2011 season, he returned to the Championship in [[2012 British Rally Championship season|2012]]. He won three out of six events in his [[Citroen DS3]] R3, meaning he won the overall title for the third time in his career.<ref>{{cite web|title= BRC 2012 Results|url=http://www.rallybrc.co.uk/index.php/mediamenu/results}}</ref> 2017 saw him crowned British Rally Champion for the fourth time.<ref>{{cite web|title= Fab Four British Rally Championship Titles For Cronin|url=https://www.msabrc.com/news/fab-four-british-rally-championship-titles-cronin/}}</ref>

In addition to competing in national events, in 2010 Cronin took part in two [[Intercontinental Rally Challenge]] events, driving a [[Proton Satria#Satria Neo (2006–present)|Proton Satria Neo S2000]] for the Proton R3 Malaysia Rally Team.<ref>{{cite web|title= Barum Czech Rally Zlin 2010 Entry List|url=http://www.ewrc-results.com/startlist.php?e=568&t=Barum-Czech-Rally-Zlin-2010}}</ref>

In 2012, Cronin also competed in three rounds of the French Citroen Racing Trophy.<ref name="Profile"/>

In 2013, Cronin won the Galway International Rally in a Subaru S11 WRC.<ref>{{cite web|title= Galway International Rally 2013 Results |url=http://results.shannonsportsit.ie/results.php?rally=GY13}}</ref>

