{{Infobox organization |name = {{lang|fr|Fédération du Sport Cycliste Luxembourgeois}} |bgcolor = <!-- header background color --> |fgcolor = <!-- header text color --> |image = Logo of the FSCL.jpg |image_border = |size = 200px |alt = <!-- alt text; see [[WP:ALT]] --> |caption = |map = <!-- optional --> |msize = <!-- map size, optional, default 200px --> |malt = <!-- map alt text --> |mcaption = <!-- optional --> |abbreviation = FSCL |motto = |formation = 1917 |extinction = <!-- date of extinction, optional --> |type = |status = <!-- ad hoc, treaty, foundation, etc --> |purpose = <!-- focus as e.g. humanitarian, peacekeeping, etc --> |headquarters = [[Strassen, Luxembourg]] |location = |coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> |region_served = [[Luxembourg]] |membership = [[Union Cycliste Internationale]] |language = <!-- official languages --> |leader_title = President |leader_name = Jean Regenwetter |main_organ = |parent_organization = <!-- if one --> |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = {{URL|http://www.fscl.lu/}} |remarks = }}
The '''Luxembourgish Cycling Federation''' ({{lang-fr|Fédération du Sport Cycliste Luxembourgeois}}), abbreviated to '''FSCL''', is the national [[sport governing body|governing body]] of [[bicycle racing|cycle racing]] in [[Luxembourg]].
The FSCL is a member of the [[Union Cycliste Internationale|UCI]], the [[Union Européenne de Cyclisme|UEC]] and the [[Luxembourgian Olympic and Sporting Committee|COSL]].
